  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Civil & Structural Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong>:</p><ul><li>Perform site planning, coordination & inspection relating to the construction project so as to ensure that project completion timeline, requirements and are met</li><li>Ensure site operations progress smoothly and on schedule, comply to all authorities requirements and standards and specifications are properly implemented</li><li>Assist PM/CM in overseeing the construction activities and progress, planning, implementation and monitoring work schedules in accordance with the detailed work program</li><li>Maintain the proper documentation of inspection forms and other follow-up inspections from RE</li><li>Coordinate the review of drawings, submission of proposal, query and design for consultant approval</li><li>Update the progress of structural works in the Progress Reports</li><li>Assist in commissioning including coordination structural engineering</li><li>Any other duties as assigned</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong>:</p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering (recognized by PE Board of Singapore)</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in local building construction industry involved in HDB/LTA projects</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore building codes and regulations and familiar with local standard quality implementation</li><li>Good leadership and communication skills, excellent organisational and problem-solving skills</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply this position via Apply Now button or email to <strong>Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p><p><em>Only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</em></p>",
